---
/**
 * context-engineering 0006 · Figure 6 — "one trace per call": the five logged
 * layers, each mapped to the stage it diagnoses.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro component so the kebab-case SVG attributes
 * render byte-for-byte (see Fig1's header for the full rationale).
 *
 * The markers this figure references (arw, arwG, arwR) are inlined into its own
 * <defs>, since the MDX has no shared <body> <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 224"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A trace logs query, retrieved doc IDs and scores, which chunks entered the window, the assembled context, and the answer, each mapped to the stage it diagnoses."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >ONE TRACE PER CALL &mdash; the answer to "which stage failed?"</text
        >
        <!-- rows -->
        <rect x="40" y="34" width="360" height="30" rx="6" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"></rect>
        <text x="52" y="53" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >1 · user query (and any rewrite)</text
        >
        <text x="588" y="53" text-anchor="end" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >&rarr; intent / pre-retrieval</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="70" width="360" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="52" y="89" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >2 · retrieved doc IDs + scores</text
        >
        <text x="588" y="89" text-anchor="end" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >&rarr; recall miss? (Lesson 1: silent)</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="106" width="360" height="30" rx="6" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"></rect>
        <text x="52" y="125" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >3 · which chunks entered the window</text
        >
        <text x="588" y="125" text-anchor="end" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >&rarr; ranking / packing / budget</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="142" width="360" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="52" y="161" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >4 · the assembled context (final prompt)</text
        >
        <text x="588" y="161" text-anchor="end" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >&rarr; assembly / order</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="178" width="360" height="30" rx="6" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="52" y="197" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >5 · the model's answer</text
        >
        <text x="588" y="197" text-anchor="end" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&rarr; generation / faithfulness</text
        >
        <!-- connectors -->
        <line x1="404" y1="49" x2="470" y2="49" stroke="#1f3a5a" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="404" y1="85" x2="430" y2="85" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="404" y1="121" x2="470" y2="121" stroke="#1f3a5a" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="404" y1="157" x2="450" y2="157" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="404" y1="193" x2="500" y2="193" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Without this, a context bug is silent (Lesson 1): the model answers confidently from wrong
        input and nothing throws. Logging each layer maps a failure to a <em>stage</em> — generic tracing
        tools (LangSmith / Phoenix-style) do this without vendor lock-in.<sup
            ><a href="#s4" id="r4">4</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
